-- European shares rise early; Adecco rallies
-- By Blaise Robinson
-- Thu May 08, 2014 03:08AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, May 8 (Reuters) - European shares rose in early trade on Thursday following dovish comments from U.S. Federal Reserve Chair Janet Yellen and better-than-expected Chinese trade figures.

Shares in Adecco SA <ADEN.VX>, the world's largest staffing company and a barometer of Europe's economic health, rose 2.9 percent after saying higher demand for its services in Germany and the UK helped revenues increase in the first three months of the year. [ID:nL6N0NU0YO] At 0704 GMT, the FTSEurofirst 300 <.FTEU3> index of top European shares was up 0.3 percent at 1,348.46 points.